annotationA: Casein kinase II subunit alpha; Casein kinases are operationally defined by their preferential utilization of acidic proteins such as caseins as substrates. The alpha chain contains the catalytic site. May participate in Wnt signaling
annotationB: Stellate protein CG33237; Unknown. In males lacking the Y chromosome, its strong overexpression leads to the appearance of proteinaceous star- shaped crystals in the primary spermatocytes causing meiotic drive, possibly by interfering with normal casein kinase 2 activity
